b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Clipdrop is best suited for image cleanup, background removal, relighting, professional editing, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. InstantArt, meanwhile, shines for free generation, model comparison, beginners, experimentation, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2020, Clipdrop describes itself as \"AI-powered image editing suite by Stability AI.\" InstantArt, established in 2023, positions itself as \"Free AI art generator with multiple Stable Diffusion models.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Clipdrop** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (7.0 vs 4.0), more features (6 vs 2), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean InstantArt is a poor choice — far from it. InstantArt excels in its own right, particularly for free generation and model comparison.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value excellent cleanup and removal tools, go with Clipdrop. If completely free to use matters more to you, InstantArt is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
